name: ContractualObligation
definition: obligation or duty that is specified in and imposed by a contract
label: contractual obligation

name: LegalObligation
definition: an obligation or duty that is enforceable by a court
label: legal obligation

name: ContractualOption
definition: contractual right that may be exercised at some point in the future, such as an option to extend a contract, or other available but not obligatory rights as defined in the contract
label: contractual option

name: ContractualRight
label: contractual right
definition: power, privilege, demand, or claim possessed by some party that is conferred by contract

name: Regulation
explanatoryNote: Many government agencies issue regulations to administer laws.
label: regulation
definition: a rule used to carry out a law

name: LegalConstruct
label: legal construct
definition: something which is conferred by way of law or contract, such as a right

name: LiabilityCapacity
definition: the ability to be sued at law
label: liability capacity

name: LegalCapacity
label: legal capacity
definition: the capability to carry out certain actions or to have certain rights together with the resources to do so

name: LegalRight
explanatoryNote: Every legal right that an individual possesses relates to a corresponding legal duty imposed on another and is recognized and delimited by law for the purpose of securing it. A legal right, if challenged, may be supported in court as recognizable and enforceable in law, statutes, regulations, or other legislative actions.
label: legal right
definition: power, privilege, demand, or claim possessed by some party by virtue of law

name: Right
definition: entitlement (not) to perform certain actions, or (not) to be in certain states; or entitlement that others (not) perform certain actions or (not) be in certain states
explanatoryNote: Rights dominate modern understandings of what actions are permissible and which institutions are just. Rights structure the form of governments, the content of laws, and the shape of morality as many now see it. To accept a set of rights is to approve a distribution of freedom and authority, and so to endorse a certain view of what may, must, and must not be done. According to the Hohfeldian incidents (Wesley Hohfeld (1879-1918)), rights are complex and consist of four major components: privilege, claim, power, and immunity.
label: right

name: Licensor
label: licensor
definition: a party who grants a license

name: ContingentObligation
definition: obligation that depends on a future event or the performance of an action
label: contingent obligation

name: Duty
definition: some obligation which exists and is imposed on some individual
label: duty

name: License
definition: grant of permission needed to do something
label: license
explanatoryNote: Note that in some cases, a license may also be considered an agreement or contract, depending on the specifics of the license and jurisdiction.

name: Claim
label: claim
explanatoryNote: Claims arise from the existence of a formal commitment between the parties or as implicitly agreed upon through the operation of law or constitution.
definition: demand or assertion made by one party on another, based on facts that, taken together, give rise to a legally enforceable right or judicial action

name: ContingentRight
label: contingent right
explanatoryNote: Contingent means that the interest, claim, or right is conditional, realized only when and if something occurs.
definition: right that depends on a future event or the performance of an action

name: LicenseIdentifier
label: license identifier
definition: an identifier associated with a license

name: ContractualCapability
label: contractual capability
definition: the capacity to enter into legally binding contracts

name: DelegatedLegalAuthority
explanatoryNote: This is always accompanied by an equal responsibility for one's actions or a failure to act.
definition: institutionalized and legal power inherent in a particular job, function, or position that is meant to enable its holder to successfully carry out his or her responsibilities, where such power has been delegated through some formal means
label: delegated legal authority

name: SignatoryCapacity
label: signatory capacity
definition: the capacity of some natural person to sign agreements on the part of some organization or legal person

name: Licensee
label: licensee
definition: a party to whom a license has been granted

name: Policy
label: policy
definition: system of principles, rules and guidelines, adopted by an organization to guide decision making with respect to particular situations and implemented via procedures or protocols to achieve stated goals

name: LitigationCapacity
label: litigation capacity
definition: the legal capacity to pursue a litigation action in law

name: ReportingPolicy
definition: policy specifying principles, rules and/or guidelines regarding some aspect of reporting
label: reporting policy

name: isLicensedBy
definition: indicates the party that has issued a particular license to some other party
label: is licensed by

name: implements
label: implements
definition: carries out or puts into effect, fulfills

name: implies
definition: strongly suggests or involves as a logical consequence based on some set of observations, facts, or events
label: implies

name: isCapacityOf
definition: identifies an individual or organization on which a given legal capacity has been conferred
label: is capacity of

name: isImpliedBy
definition: indicates something that is strongly suggested by something else, such as a logical consequence based on some set of observations, facts, or events
label: is implied by

name: isConferredOn
label: is conferred on
definition: indicates a party to which some benefit or right has been granted

name: isImplementedBy
definition: indicates something that is carried out, incorporated or put into effect by
label: is implemented by

name: licenses
label: licenses
definition: issues a license required in order to perform some task, provide some service, exercise some privilege, or pursue some line of business or occupation to some party

name: hasCapacity
label: has capacity
definition: identifies an individual or organization that has some ability and availability to carry out certain actions, or has certain rights or obligations
